# ADR-007 – Why Multi-AI Development Workflow

## Status

Accepted

---

## Context

Atlas is intended to demonstrate professional software engineering practices as well as modern AI-assisted development.

Large Language Models have different strengths.

Rather than relying on a single AI assistant throughout the development lifecycle, Atlas adopts a structured multi-AI workflow where each assistant has a clearly defined engineering role.

The objective is to improve software quality while ensuring that all architectural decisions remain under human control.

---

## Decision

Atlas adopts the following engineering workflow.

### ChatGPT

Role: Solution Architect

Responsibilities:

- Product vision
- Architecture
- Technology selection
- Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)
- Sprint planning
- Solution design
- Engineering governance

ChatGPT is responsible for deciding *what* should be built and *why*.

---

### GitHub Chat (Copilot)

Role: Implementation Engineer

Responsibilities:

- Implement approved designs
- Generate production code
- Create unit tests
- Suggest refactoring
- Follow project coding standards
- Use project context documentation

GitHub Chat is responsible for implementing approved designs.

---

### Claude Code

Role: Senior Engineer / Code Reviewer

Responsibilities:

- Review implementations
- Identify architectural inconsistencies
- Improve maintainability
- Strengthen validation
- Expand test coverage
- Challenge unnecessary complexity

Claude reviews implementations before they are committed.

---

### Human Developer

Role: Technical Lead

Responsibilities:

- Make architectural decisions
- Review AI suggestions
- Accept or reject changes
- Maintain engineering quality
- Approve commits and releases

No AI assistant has authority to make final engineering decisions.

---

## Workflow

```
Requirements
      │
      ▼
Architecture (ChatGPT)
      │
      ▼
Implementation (GitHub Chat)
      │
      ▼
Code Review (Claude)
      │
      ▼
Human Approval
      │
      ▼
Tests
      │
      ▼
Git Commit
      │
      ▼
Release
```

---

## Consequences

### Advantages

- Clear separation of responsibilities.
- Reduced architectural drift.
- Better code quality through independent review.
- Stronger automated testing.
- Human ownership of all important decisions.
- Repeatable engineering process.

### Risks

- Slightly longer development cycle.
- Requires discipline to maintain roles.
- AI suggestions may occasionally conflict and require judgement.

---

## Future Evolution

Additional AI assistants may be introduced where they provide clear value, for example:

- Security review
- Documentation generation
- Performance optimisation
- Automated release note generation

The core principle remains unchanged:

AI assists.

Humans decide.